,Recommended,518790,31312202,Posted: 22 April,all,rocket2guns,"This is the most beautiful game I have played in some time. I would say that the game is quite modestly priced for what it provides, but it is clearly a hunting experience more than a hunting game - so it's not going to be a game for everyone.Headshots at low calibre ""bug""Most of the negative reviews I see claim ""bugs"" for what is actually how ballistics work in the real world. Example: lower calibre headshots will often not kill an animal. Many of the animals use their heads for fighting for goodness sake! I have (in real life) shot goats in the head and have the animal up and leave. The skull on many animals is very thick and therefore you're aiming for the heart/lungs.Negatives:- The Skill/Perk/XP/Points system is insane. Obviously, this is a leftover from the game having P2W/F2P mechanics which I am glad they dropped. But it's left us with a pretty terrible and confusing system that is incredibly convoluted. It doesn't rise to the point of a negative reivew, but it's close for me.- Multiplayer is a little buggy at times. Not overly so, and it's been acknowledged by the devs and they're clearlying targeting patches to this. It's still very playable and enjoyable.- The range of weapons available is pretty low.- The amount of equipment available to upgrade you weapons was much lower than I was expecting. While some of this would be quite ""game-y"", I was expecting being able to customize your weapons and equipment more according to how you wanted to play.Positives:+ The game is the most beautiful game I have played a in a long time, hands down. They're using dynamic color grading, volumetric lights, dynamic shadows... I mean just everything and the results are superb!+ The map(s) are staggering in their scale and attention to detail. They're hand made and they are huge. Much bigger than ArmA.+ The performance of the game on a high-end PC is excellent. Don't expect to run at ULTRA on current gen hardware, and don't be mad about that! The game is made in such a way that it's going to grow with hardware and that's great.+ The pacing of the game is really superb. It strikes an excellent balance between requiring patience and keeping something happening to the player.+ Post kill review screen. You see the pose, entry, and damage modelling for what you killed. Absolutely amazing and makes your kill ""story"" fantastic.+ Tracking is exciting and the classic ""easy to do hard to master"". This is a well designed mechanic that leads to excellent pacing.ConclusionIf you are looking for an arcade game, this is not for you. But if you are looking for a hunting game this is a fantastic find. Even better with friends! It's modest price is worth is alone for how beautiful the terrain is to explore."
