76561197977704937,Not Recommended,518790,31980294,Posted: 26 May,all,Fancy,"The game has much potential.  Graphically, it is great.  The two biggest issues that drove me away:1) Animal population density (i.e. too many animals in too small of an area) leading to a very small TBK (time between kills).  I get that people have short attention spans, but to me, hunting should involve more time spent calling in and stalking than this game presents.  You can currently bag 10+ animals in an hour of playing.  This drastically takes away from the immersion and reward of each kill.2) Bugged animals.  I don't expect perfection in any game these days.  But when 50% of the animals I track down run into each other, or get stuck on environmental obstacles (e.g. running endlessly into the side of a tree or mountain) this removes most of the reward in the hunt, and again, removes most all of the immersion.Properly fix those two issues and this would likely be one of the best hunting games ever made."
,Recommended,518790,30228974,Posted: 27 February,all,NaturalDisaster,"It's as step up from theHunter: Classic in some areas and a step back in others, however it's a good platform to build on like they did with Classic.Pros:- Updated graphics, some of the best scenery you will see in any game.- Hunting pressure, new mechanic to make it difficult to hunt in areas you've already hunted.- Improved animal behaviors. Animals will give warning calls, mating calls, and can be found in large heards.  There was also the addition of ""need zones"" that you can discover such as sleeping zones, drinking and feeding zones where you can find specific species at certain hours of the day.- Night hunting, with the help of a headlamp.- CoTW replaces a membership pay model of Classic with a RPG system that makes you gradually unlock new weapons and equipment through XP, also has a pretty neat skills/perks system that really adds some flavor to hunting.Cons:- Lacks the diversity of theHunter: Classic. Only 2 hunting reserves at the time of launch, a handful of weapons and a pretty small roster of game to hunt.- Scoring system seems wonky, not a huge fan of the ""consecutive harvests"" idea. The game awards senseless killing and not being patient and selective like it should be.- Small features like trophy shots and trophy galleries not available at this time. Guessing in the future? Not sure why something like this would be cut from the game.- Performance issues, some people complaining about crashes/bugs. Latest patch addressed some issues though.-  No mobile tree stands, or tents. You have to discover outposts around the map and use them to fast travel."
