76561198044858929,Recommended,518790,35051245,Posted: 18 September,all,SirCrezzy,"I wasn't sure about putting out a review for this game just yet as I haven't got a HUGE amount of hours in the game, however i feel due to the long time I put into Thehunter Classic I feel that my currently amount of time has given me enough insight to be able to give a full, proper review of this game. I am however going to keep this short as super long reviews aren't my fortae unless i'm getting paid for it.Well what can I say about this game. It's very realistic. This is to say its realistic coming from the eyes and ears of someone who has never hunted IRL. The game feel and looks and sounds exactly how the wild actually sounds. The wind blowing through the trees, the chirping of distant birds, the dripping of rain during a storm, and of course the echoing shout of a gunshot and the thrilling thud of a deer hitting the floor. All the sounds make me feel like I really am in the German wilderness.The graphics are extremely beautiful. I have taken more screenshots of nothingness in this game than I will of interesting things happening in other games. You will be walking along, minding your own business when all of a sudden a vista framed in trees calls to you. It begs you to take a picture. It makes you feel as though you truly have stumbles upon a sight that no one has ever seen before. It is as thrilling as the hunt.The gameplay is not perfect at this time. Sometimes when you are tracking the calls of a Roe Deer, you hear the thumping of hooves only to turn around and see a majestic creature running continuously into a tree only to take 4 point blank shots with a .243 rifle with soft point bullets and still run. The bugs are here but are getting less and less apparent as time goes on.Oh dear... this has already gone on too long. My poor little fingers are aching and if I type one more paragraph someone is going to have to give me lots of money. I will however say this, the game in my opinon is fantastic and a great improvement over the classic. Get this game and stop reading (assuming you havent already stopped....I would have)"
