,Recommended,518790,30188234,Posted: 25 February,all,Moose,"Shot a fallow deer 5 times, tracked it for over 1 real time hour, game crashed before I found it. 10/10 too much waterEDIT:TL;DR - Enjoyable, feels like a beta but very pretty with an iffy interface, less of a hunting game and more an animal shooting game. Bows are OP. No microtransactions.After putting more time into this, I feel I can write a proper and serious review. At the time of writing, this game functions like beta. That said, despite being riddled with bugs and occasional crashes (though your mileage may vary on bugginess) this game is a graphically superb and worthy sibling to theHunter Classic, and I don't regret my purchase. My only major complaint is that they somehow managed to be less realistic in this game than Classic with both the general feel of the game and with animal behaviors - I feel I can describe it best in the way that Diablo 3 is not a dungeon crawler like D2, but a very large loot run. Similarly, you are placed in the vast reserve (and I do mean vast, the maps are colossal) with free reign over a never-ending hunt. It doesn't feel like hunting to me, it feels like animal shooting. Veterans of theHunter Classic (or even other hunting games, I suppose) might understand better than someone fresh to the genre.Animals, particularly female deer, are still dumb as walking rocks with the added bonus of sometimes running you over on accident in their zeal to be the first to stand as close to you as possible. Bright side? They don't seem to magnetize toward you anymore - they go where the call was and stick around the immediate area. You're free to sprint like a madman with (seemingly) little consequence. In fact, it seems rewarding by the warning calls provided by animals, alerting you to their rough location. Just crouch and spam your callers. Move toward them for increased efficiency. Animals also seem to be very nonchalant about gunfire, even within ranges where they would probably reasonably hear it. They also seem to not mind returning to the same area where you butchered several herd members already. That said - the hunting pressure system seems to mostly work. Animals outside the group (if there was one) you killed from are very unlikely to enter the area when attracted to calls or scents. They do, on occasion, wander through to get somewhere else, though.So far, weapons handle reasonably well and have satisfying sounds and animations, though I personally find the kick-up of recoil to sometimes be laughably extreme as an avid hunter in real life. The .243 is not as woefully pathetic as in Classic, and will absolutely do the work you need it to (until you can get the .270. Get it.). However, I recommend polymer tip bullets when available. They are a pleasant step up from the standard soft points, but certainly not a critical upgrade. Bows, however, seem grossly overpowered at the moment. Flesh wounds will have deer bleeding out in times comparable to decent rifle shots.The interface is a bit cumbersome and lacks information (e.g. current weapon scores outside of the shop, experience until next level, return to main menu button) that I would like to have access to, although this is more of a personal gripe than a point against the game. Most of the nitpicky issues I have with menus and interface are personal beyond being unrefined. The map also has the tendency to find itself focused on anywhere except where you are when opened.If I sound harsh on this game, it's not because these are glaring faults that should dissuade you from buying. This is a good game for the state it's in, but realize that it does have issues. I can recommend this to veterans of Classic that want a more streamlined and immediate hunting experience without fussing through menus and launchers or simply want to support Avalanche and Expansive Worlds. It's more of theHunter, what can I say? If you're on the fence or new to this series, perhaps stick with Classic until this game is fleshed out more."
76561198034457388,Not Recommended,518790,30019657,Posted: 18 February,all,FoXRuN,"Well lets start with specs.MSi Z97 Gaming 5 MoboG.SKILL Ripjaws X Series 16GBIntel Core i7 4790K Devil's CanyonCooler Master Hyper 212 HSFUFSP Group Aurum Gold 750wMSi GTX 960 Gaming 4G (x2) in Sli2x 250gb Samsung Evo 850 SSD - Raid 01x 500gb Samsung Evo 850 - StorageWindows 10 OSWith my current PC setup I have 0 issues with running on ultra 1440p as far as graphics are concerned.The game itself is beautiful and very detailed.  I can't say that I have seen a hunting game with better graphics.  The inital tutorial (If you use it)  was very straight forward and gives you good information in regards to gameplay.  Full controller support is a + but I didnt see any tutorial telling you how to better learn the controls if using a gamepad.  I opted for mouse and keys after discovering how clunky the controls felt on the 360 controller.Played the game and streamed it for a good 7 hours solid on launch day.  During the time playing I noticed more flaws then animals.  The deer seemed to be more responsive to calls then in classic.  They will literally run up withing 10m of you just to immediatly spook and run away.  So keep your eyes peeled for that and make sure you dont call them in when they are slowly heading your direction or they may just run right to you.Huntermate bug.  Having the huntermate in your hand and then pressing H to hide equipment swapping around then pressing Tab to bring up the huntermate actually brings up what looks like the face of an otterbax that your phone has fallen out of!   Whats this?!  Sure you can Tab around and get it back easily but hmmm.People with a poor quality internet connection, or beloew requirement PC can still play.  But be aware that you will Croush, Walk, and Run at least 10x slower then anyone else in game and you will rubberband around and have glitchy player animations.  I whitnessed all of this while playing with a friend that I am going to build a new PC for.I unlocked the bow!   YES! now that I've earned 10,000 and change I am going to buy the bow and some arrows and give that a shot.    Supprise Supprise....  I have EXPLODING arrows?!   While luring in an animal there I was.... Tucked under a tree for better cover and got my doe lured in at around 15m away.   I draw my bow and wait for her to turn.   Booom!  I fired my arrow to notice a flash and a giant puff of smoke come off the deer I shot.   Realistic?!  Hardly.While in a game and checking out the menu I noticed there is NO way of going back to home screen.  You simply have to Alt+F4 or you have to X out of the game and restart if you wish you start a new hunt or go from singleplayer to multiplayer.There are no micro-transactions in-game and I feel this is a good thing!  I feel that with how they marketed the game you should have to work for your gear which in turn will make it more enjoyable.  Simply being able to hop in and buy the guns you want, and anything you need with a micro-transaction seems to bring out the boredom and fast.I think in total having TheHunter (Classic) since 2011 and putting in over 300 hours on steam and well over 400 hours with the launcher from the site.  If you are looking into a new hunting game and have not tried TheHunter (Classic) then that is the game I would go for.There are many other glitches and bugs I have not mentioned in this post for Call of the Wild but believe me when I tell you they are there.  Expansive Worlds released this game too early and didn't spend the quality time required from a dev team to iron out majority of the glitches and bugs you are bound to discover if you download this game.Sure you are going to have bugs in a game. But for it not to be announced as early-access or beta.  There are too many in this game for it to be launched as a complete title.TheHunter (Classic) also has a vast array of species for you to hunt.  There are only 2 reserves and limited species to hunt on Call of the Wild as of yet.I'll leave the decision making to you the gamers, but if I had to choose now after only being 7 hours in.  This game needs some serious work.  Oh.... and waterfoul hunting.  ;)-FoX"
