,Recommended,518790,30308347,Posted: 3 March,all,OddJawb,"This is both a great game, and kind of meh at the same time.My first impressions of the game is its beautiful - followed by - ""♥♥♥♥ me, this games setting has me hunting in europe? i've only ever hunted in the backwoods of the USA.... wonder what this will be like?"" followed quickly by a murdering rampage though the hills, :D.  in the span of 100 minutes I killed 5 Roe deer, 2 foxes, and 1 fallow deer.  But thats where the game starts to break down.The Good - This game is great for casual hunting, and by that i mean its a great pick up and shoot stuff hunter - not  much required in the way of getting started. You are given a decent set up right from the get go, you arn't required to buy hunting licenses or anything like that, and since the game is set up as a Arcade shooter - you can kill as manythings as you want - no bag limits :D.The Bad - For anyone looking for a more realistic hunting game this isn't going to be your bread and butter. This game is very beautiful however, it is not a deer hunter replacement. I never had to sight my gun, prep for my trip, buy hunting licenses, there was nothing in this game that made it feel like anything more than a casual arcade mode hunting game. Deer and wildlife are extreamly easy to track from the very begining since tracks light up and glow for you to track the game.The Ugly -  Its a bit buggy in a few areas - I got attacked by a rock and lost half my health walking down a steep hill :P. Another kind of disapointing feature is the scorecard system - For example, I shot a deer and missed its lung (the hold your breath is extramly short starting out) and shot the deer in the stomach - it didnt go down right away as to be expected and ran off and died around 200 meters away. Upon collecting the ""Trophy"" A score card is presented and then I was given a rather high score for botching this kill. Most anyone who hunts knows this was not a clean kill - the animal,  if this were in real life,  suffered immensly before dying of bloodloss and exhuastion.  I further tested this out and shot a deer resting in the face - Bang ""trick shot"" achievement - thats when it set in for me that this game was not going to come close to being a deer hunter replacment.All in all though - its a great game that seems to have a team deadicated to fixing the game and improving it - its just not going to scratch the itch of being a real hunting simulator to get you through waiting for the next hunting season."
