76561198139653472,Recommended,518790,30232586,Posted: 27 February,all,12jakemetz,"I had just spotted my first decent buck in Layton Lake and observed, attempting to get closer for a better shot. However, he quickly spooked and bolted off into the underbrush. I tracked him, but eventually gave up and decided to head for a nearby observation point and take in the scenery.I'd like to say, this game has perfectly captured how it feels to be in the woods. I hike occasionally during the summer and this is the first game I've ever seen that had me convinced my character was actually in a forest instead of just a clump of trees. The underbrush is great and the topogrophy is excellent. The way the lighting interacts with the trees and brush is absolutely perfect.Back to ingame, I continued along a path leading to the lookout tower. Then my attention was brought straight forward by the warning grunt of a black bear. I quickly dropped into a crouch and raised my rifle. Though some brush, I could see a bear with a cinnamon coat quartering towards me, coming along the path maybe 45 yards away. I lined up the reticle with the front of his shoulder, held my breath, pulled the trigger. He took a few more steps along the path, so I fired again, dropping him in his tracks.This is what you get when you purchase this product. A convincing virtual world and a rewarding experience. At times it's a painfully slow burner, but when you finally get that perfect shot you know that the game didn't give it to you. You earned it.P.S. to fans of turkey hunting, waterfowling and upland birds: They aren't currently included in the game but I have a strong suspicion they'll make their way in at some point.EDIT: I should mention there did seem to be a large infestation of bugs when the game was first released but it has been patched multiple times since release and I have yet to experience any game breaking bugs, just a few very minor graphical glitches."
