76561197970617282,Recommended,518790,30459343,Posted: 11 March,all,Jagella,"The Hunter Call of the Wild is essentially a first-person shooter. Unlike most shooters, though, you don't get shot. You shoot or try tho shoot game like deer, foxes, and bison. You hunt this game in a forest in Europe. This forest is very beautiful with lush vegetation and has weather effects like wind, rain, and fog. The terrain is varied being fairly flat in some places and mountainous in other places. The forest is huge and can take a long time to traverse. Fortunately there are outposts scattered about the forest. Once discovered, you can fast travel to other outposts in other areas of the map.On the downside, the game requires a lot of patience. You can play for an hour or more without seeing any game. When you do see game, it is very skittish and will run off even when you are far away from it. If you do shoot an animal it may run off leaving you empty handed. A bug in the game sometimes causes the animals to run in place. You can shoot them point blank without killing them.Is The Hunter for you? If you like something that can simulate hunting, then it might be a good choice. It does lend a feeling that you are actually stalking animals in the woods. When you do get a kill, it can be a satisfying experience. The map can be fun just to explore. For those of you who want much to do much of the time, this game probably won't please you.Is The Hunter for me? I've found that it does get better the more I play. It is a bit different from most of the shooters I play, and I've been looking for something different. I'm also pleased with the graphics. I'd say The Hunter is fair, and that's why I rate it three stars.You may wish to consider Far Cry 3, Far Cry 4, and Far Cry Primal. Theses games allow you to hunt game along with battling enemies. Unlike The Hunter, these games are much faster paced and animals much less difficult to hunt."
