oot hill)The game has a lot wrong with it right now, I have no doubt that the game was rushed out. A lot of the problems seem like they could be quick fixes, but these problems should have NOT been in the release. And testing for more than an hour or two would have pinpointed the problems easily. But with all of that the game is still great, I have enjoyed spending the whole day on the game and haven’t felt bored. So for a new buyer I would have to say hold off until they fix a few of the bugs. The game is not unplayable by any means but I feel like some standards need to be held, especially for a $30 game."
