76561197972278924,Recommended,518790,30079282,Posted: 21 February,all,Deicide666ra,"I rarely do reviews, but I figured this game with it's current mitigated score could use a straight to the point review, I hope this helps you make a decision.First off a little about me, I'm no real life hunter and this is my first hunting game. I had been interested by the different games that existed before this one, but the general consensus seemed to be that they were all rip-offs, trying to squeeze the players out of their RL money with endless micro transactions and DLC's, etc.This game is gorgeous, they really nailed the outdoors feeling really well. I don't think I can name a game that has more beautiful trees/forests, it looks fantastic and the performance is also very good. I'm running it at high details (not ultra) and it's absolutely amazing and runs smooth on my mid-level gaming laptop (GTX970M, 16 gigs ram, i7 cpu).There are bugs though... LOTS of bugs, but so far, none are game-breaking. Animals sometimes get stuck in trees and rocks... There are bunnies or whatever that do a stupid amount of noise that doesn't sound natural. You can't walk up a 30% incline (approx). Your walking and run speed is affected by your FPS (this is most noticeable in multiplayer, reducing image quality will make you run faster). I could go on, the game kind of feels like it should be a beta or early release, they definitely still had a lot of ironing out to do before calling it gold IMHO, but despite all this, it's still an amazing game.So far, I'm getting my money's worth, there is no doubt, it's a unique experience, I really enjoy it."
