76561197968507675,Recommended,518790,30533780,Posted: 15 March,all,Wolfy,"This has got to be one of the best, most annoying games I've played in recent years. The hunting experience is fantastic and the gameplay is a joy, however the constant 'quality of life' issues just make it a hassle to play.The maps are huge and detailed however movement speed is glacial and there are no vehicles. Fast travel is limited to a handful of spaced out locations that must be unlocked by spending hours walking to them.Huge amounts of grinding are required to unlocked better equipment, for some bizarre reason the developer has felt the need to restrict players as to their style of play, perhaps to add longevity, but I would have appreciated the option to just unlock everything, after all, I am the player and it is my game.There are some bizarre design choices, like the 'consecutive harvest' feature. In short, if you want to get high scores for your harvests you need to rack up multiple harvests beforehand for no apparent reason.The UI is awkward and unclear especially re movement speeds and noise as well as visibility (apparently using a controller is the best way to play, unacceptable for a PC game).Bugs are frequent, although the developers are working hard to iron them out, however as plenty of other reviewers have stated, the game should not have been released in the state that it is (or at least, for the price that it is).There is no steam workshop/mod support that I can see. This would be by far the easiest way to start fixing bugs and letting players customise their experience, and is the lifeblood of PC gaming imho that adds years to the longevity of any game.I've really enjoyed the hours I've put in so far, but I'm going to take a break until the game becomes a bit more accessible, otherwise I fear I will just grow to resent it.I would certainly recommend the game, but perhaps err on the side of caution and wait for a sale or additional patches to come out."
