76561198300367467,Recommended,518790,33458768,Posted: 11 July,all,theartist,"this is my review. (no seriously, how does one begin a review..?)look of the game:the game looks beautiful. i recommend watching a few video's about it, the lighting and landscape are beautiful.the characters lack personality. and their animations are not the greatest. but it's a hunting game, not an rpg.the animals are nice and really realistic (the looks), but sometimes the movement is a bit clucky. not gamebreaking though.gameplay:the core mechanics are good, you can play the game very well and i've quite a few hours in it.there is things like bulletdrop, and a lot of other things that make it really simulator like. it's not running around and shooting things.the core game is really about hunting, there are missions (quests) but they work a bit clunky and i find myself mostly hunting and leveling up for more gear.bugs:if you've read other reviews you know that there are quite few bugs. they mostly spawn into excistence after new content is added. i find that the gamebreaking ones get fixed very fast. the small ones keep floating around longer that you would expect is needed.but keep in mind, this isn't a big game with a enormous dev team. and the devs are quite involved in the community and listening. which is really nice.comunity:i mentioned before that the devs are quite active in the comunity, the playerbase is nice, not toxic at all.there are streams from the devs every week.there are quite a few players with other languages, so far i've seen germans, chinese, a few eastern Europeans and a few russians. but the English comunity is dominating as far as i can see.overall.i personally like the game, the devs are active in the comunity, the game is fun to play. even if you don't like to hunt all the time it's fun to explore the landscape and discover.keep in mind, it's not an action based game, not really fast paced. the game has a little lore but its main focus is the hunting.multiplayer is right now kinda buggy, although they are working on it.if you plan to play only multiplayer you might want to wait do some more research.the bugs can be annoying, so if you expect an perfect game. you might look elsewhere.payment model:there are no pay to win mechanics in place. in game currency isn't buyable with real money.they release dlc's which are paid. they add more content but are not needed♥♥♥♥♥♥♥for enjoying the game.they have released a few free dlc's too and the paid ones are not that expensive at all.overall i give it an 8 out of 10.some notes:1: the next patch will help collorblind people spot tracks by giving recollor options.2: i've bought the atv dlc, it's usefull but not needed to enjoy the game, i advise to buy the core game and dicide if you want to buy any dlc's later. the tents dlc i didn't buy, and i heard it's a bit buggy sometimes, no expirience with it myself so ask someone who does.3: i've bought it on sale.4: i'm young but i've seen that the game has quite a few older people playing it too. might be nice if your older to know.(not only though)and last, i'm not a native English speaker and steam disables my auto correct.. so i probably made a few grammar mistakes. deal with it :P"
