,Recommended,518790,31563088,Posted: 5 May,all,Ewok126,"I have over 400 plus hours in the game and now here is my review.After having a stroke in November this past year, it is one of the few games I can play. Please overlook any typos I may have.The game came with alot of bugs in the begining but the team seems very commited to fixing these issues and they seem to be very quick in listening to the community (WITH IN REASON) meaning if the community is being asinine then the openion is moot) and they respond in kind very quickly. I have been very lucky to not have as many issues as some. My PC is not a huge rig gaming system and have no idea on why I have not had the issues that alot of others do. I just mark it up to luck.Now to the game.The graphics in this game is Fantastic to say the least.The ambiant sounds is totaly astounding. For me it is very submersive since I can not go walking in the woods any more in real life.GamePlay: For me it is laking in realisum. Examples: The range finder is worthless at the moment for me. Here is why, I seem to notice there is no bullet drop so there is no need to range out an animal. If you can hit it by aiming dead on at any distance say 20 meters vs 300 meters depending on the weapon. For example at 300 meters I can hit an animal with the 7mm and with a 338 with No bullet drop so there is no reason to compensate for distance. Now in using a pistol or bow as long as the animal is with in the suggested range  of the weapon you will hit it. The bow seems to behave more realistic with distance having drop the further out an animal is. There was an issue to where if you shot an animal at point blank range with a high powered rifle you would just get a flesh wound but they seem to have fixed this some what. Other examples inclued being able to call back a wounded animal. I have seen in real life being able to call back a spooked animal but never a wounded animal but that could just be my lack of experiance which granted I do have alot of hunting experiance in real life.  The game is lacking in bullet behavior for each weapon so for example a 7mm vs a 338. In real life the 7mm has a flater trajectory than the 338  the 223 is even flatter than the 7mm at shorter distance but wind and such does not come in to play in game. Real life a 223 would be more acurate than that of a 7mm as long as there is no wind and shorter distance. The more heavy the bullet the less wind affects it but less knock down power at great distance due to the loss of vilosity over distance and time. These are the things I feel the game is missing for realisum. In closing I will wrap it up in a nutshell.Graphics Stunning, Sound stuning, Realisum ehh needs work. Bugs there is quite a few but the Team seems to be working hard on them,  I think that over time this game will hit its full ptential as long as the team stays diligent. I would buy this game again.Disclaimer: My perception is my Reality, Your perception is your reality, WE ALL  PERCEIVE TINGS DIFFERENTLY"
