76561197976850287,Recommended,518790,30714454,Posted: 24 March,all,epideath,"Great game even thoug I had a very rocky start. For the bad part first, this game would constantly crash on me every 5-90 minutes, I had changed from ultra to lowest possible graphics settings to no avail. After the latest patch I thought the developers would fix this problem. Well still constant crashes. So I decided to go another route, and look a bit more at my hardware. I installed a utility that came with my graphics card, and lowered the clock speed down and limited the temperature, LOW AND BEHOLD success!!, So I looked further and noticed the graphics card was getting a bit high, not really out of the norm for cards nowadays though. A little further testing and I ended up changing the speed of my GPU fan to aggressive. This game is now rock solid on ULTRA setting and getting over 30fps. So just a note to others about crashes, you may want to look in your own backyard a little like I did.NOW FOR THE GOOD. I'm not a hunter at all in real life. But this game is relaxing and fun. I really like the missions as they get you motivated to explore and as they progressivly get harder it takes more concentration and patience. I'm glad that I get to enjoy the game now without the fear of a crash, so I can take my time esploring and looking for outposts, and other POI's. I'm only level 20 but I'm having a great time. Keep in mind that I got 70+ hours in this game even with the constant crashes I had previously, that has to mean something! I can't wait to unlock more items to play around with. I thought bow hunting would be hard but I was happily suprised that it was not a whole lot harder than a gun. I can't wait to see how far my lonest shot will be eventullay and what kind of trophy kills I can get. So much to do. :)I want to thank the developers of this game and I can't wait to see further improvements and DLC's in the future."
