 deep and they wouldn't stop coming back until I dropped about 15-20 of them (wish I recorded it). The only thing that kept me alive was by jumping up on a rock so they wouldn't trample me to death. For some reason they took off after killing so many. Not sure exactly why they decided to move on. The stampede sounds like rolling thunder. I originally thought it was a motorcycle outside and took my headphones off a few times to make sure it was the game.- I now wander around with the 30-30, 7mm, and bow. I haven't unlocked everythig but this seems like a good combination for anything I come accross.- Some of the missions are really hard and have given up on a few of them as they seem bugged and others have complained about them as well.- If you come across this review and are on the fence, give it a try. If you play less than 2 hours, you can still get a refund. I feel that $30 (current price) would give you 3 hours of entertainment at a movie theater (with consessions) but this game will keep you entertained for tens, if not, hundreds of hours.Overall, it's a great game and excited to see the game evolve as bugs are squashed and more DLCs are created. I'm looking forward to birds (mallards and geese), small game (rabbits), equipment (tree stand etc.), and new weapons (17 hmr please)."
