76561198045231522,Recommended,518790,30016446,Posted: 18 February,all,Deximer,"It's great so far. I was skeptical, like so many others, from both the mixed reviews and the arcadey looking YouTube videos. I've also played the Hunter classic for a long time and have invested many hours in it. I know some of what I'll put here has already been said, but I feel the game deserves another positive review.The main issue that caused me to hesitate on purchasing was the arcadey look. It mainly comes from the videos having every single visual clue turned on, all of which you can disable. If you simply disable the visual audio clues, and change the track clues to just glow and not the bouncy animation - you are basically right back at the Hunter classic in terms of play. You don't even have that cheat mode of seeing the animal call on the pda and then clicking in the area.  You need to determine from sound direction alone where the call came from. These 2 elements basically remove the arcadey feel just by themselves.Not sure of all the bugs people claim to be having, I have encountered only a couple in my 12 hours of play and none of them were that serious. One of them required a restart, but that was after 3-4 hours of straight play with no issues. The tracks disappeared.Graphics look great, it's awesome that the clock just keeps going and you can go all through the day and night if you choose or rest to speed it back up to your desired time. The night time with the moonlight is especially nice.Don't want to keep going on and on, but again, if your main reservation is the arcadey look - it's worth taking a look for yourself to see, I didn't want to pass it up simply based on other's reviews and I'm glad I didn't."
