76561197977088462,Recommended,518790,33101593,Posted: 1 July,all,>>RAGE<<,"First of all this game is not for people who are impatient and who want to do some run and gun.This game is for people who like walking through a beautiful virtual nature with all of its sounds and atmosphere.I played TheHunter Classic for a long time, now I discovered The Hunter Call of the wild and I bought it.At first I thought about getting a refund for it because it looked blurry and flickering.I am sensitive for flickering and flickering makes me feel sick.So I tried reshade (just google it) which adds various effect to the game. With this I added some effects and managed to minimize the blur and flickering and I decided to give the game a chance.I played the game 3 hours at a time until I had to stop. This game is so amazing and looks amazing. I did really not expect this.At first I was stunned by the beautiful virtual nature. It looks amazing and it sounds amazing.I just stood still and listened to all the noises around me. You can hear any kind of noise which you can hear when you go into the forest (animals, wind, rain, rustle of the undergrowth, crunchy stones...).Second there is a great weather system. The weather keeps changing from foggy, to sunny, to rainy or to stormy.When you see dark clouds appearing in the sky then you can be sure that it will soon start raining.There is also a day/night cycle and the game feels totally spooky during night. You can hear owls in the distance and bats flying around. I played a lots of survival games and during nights it always feels like zombies or mutants would appear xD.I know that this is a hunting simulation but the simulation of the wilderness is just amazing.When you want to hunt down some animals then this is not a easy job. The animals can hear you, smell you and see you. You always have to be very careful or the animal will just run away (like it happened to me a lot :D).You can lure them by using varios lures or you can track them by following their calls or tracks.But do not expect that there will be an animal every 5 minutes. You need to be patient an careful.I have been waiting for about 30 minutes in a hideout until a deer appeared. This was not boring for me, it was thrilling for me.Even when you spot an animal, you have to be patient. You cannot just shoot easily on 100 meters at the beginning of the game.It needs to come closer until you can shoot it. But even when it is close enough it is not easy to shoot it.You need to hold your breath and then you have to aim carefuly for the zones where you want to hit it. You cannot just shoot the foot and then it dies. There are different zones where you should hit it.If you do not hit the deadly zones then it will bleed and run away and then you have to trace it. This process takes a lot of time so you should better be patient and hit the correct zone.I also like the sounds of the weapons. They sound quite real. Everything is quiet, then you aim and... boom... a shot breaks the silence. This feels really great and also contributes to the atmosphere.This game is a real hunting simulation and I really like it.I did not find any bugs or technical issues yet but I hope the developers will add more options for graphics so that you do not have to use reshade to make the game look great.http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=961423211http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=961422611http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=961422953"
