76561197979161262,Recommended,518790,34215238,Posted: 13 August,all,jimster686,"This game is suprisingly good, if you can switch from FarCry to a hunting, and ""enjoying a trophy"" - mode. The skill tree really makes a difference. You level up, buy better weapons, get more skilled with all of it, and have an amazing landscape and weather system. If you just run full speed through this, you won't see much, because the entire forest will run away ;-)If you take your time, patience, this can even be rewarding for a Farcry player. Most things come close to reality in this, concerning the act of hunting (I'm a hunter, so I know). Thunderstorms and rain/wind are most immersive. A bit too loud for my taste, but you ""buy it"". After a week now, I tried other hunting games, the classic and the one with slow-mo, but this here is the most authentic and has the best graphic/artwork. Simple things as the ""walking sounds"" are absolutely fine in this game, compared to many others.Critique: This base game needs much more, to keep you going after you got the most important skills. New DLCs, (the ATV/quad DLC is very useful, the fast-travel tent also very good), but this is just for convenience. This needs more animals, maybe brown bears, grizzly..., birds you can pick (not just call rabbits critters like rats without trophy), maybe add taxidermy to mount trophies in a / your lodge, like with the classic game, trophy snapshot is missing.Missions: Missions like ""get 2 bears in a picture"" or ""get this fallow deer in a picture with Lake whatsoever in the background"", this is reeaally tedious ! Maybe someone likes that, I can't stand it.I'd like missions like ""find this crual man-eating bear with the crazy scar and put him down, get a trophy shot and so on..."""
