,Recommended,518790,33939411,Posted: 31 July,all,WohlfePac,"Hey everyone this is WohlfePac and this is my review for The Hunter Call of the Wild. First off this is a really fun game. I love hunting in real life and this game goes right along with that. You get rifles, shotguns, pistols, compound bows, and all kinds of tools and calls. Pros: It's a great open world experience. The graphics are pretty good and the calmness of walking through the woods is very relaxing. I tend to play this game when i just want to relax and not have people jumping out of every corner trying to kill me. I really like the tent and blind dlc. I don't use the. Blinds very much but the tent allows you to buy stuff from pretty much anywhere. You don't have to run back to your cabin to buy or store something, you just drop your tent, step inside and buy something. You can also sleep there too which is really handy. You can also fast travel back to it if you get too far away. The gun mechanics are very good and I don't mean to brag but I killed a deer from over 200 yards away. I'm excited for the atv dlc because it's a huge map and just walking somewhere takes forever! Luckily I'll be picking that up once it releases.Cons: there are a few cons and one of them being the map has a small glitch that when u set a way point it doesn't put it on the spot where you clicked on, it puts it just off to one side of it or just below it. Doesn't seem bad but when u get where u wanted the marker is about 100 yards away from where u wanted it (a little exaggerated but still frustrating). Also it seems kinda stupid to have to pay to sleep. Yea and it's not very cheap. I think it was just under 200 credits just to sleep. I'm hoping they'll remove this in an update. Also there are only 2 bows, 6 rifles, 4 shotguns, and 4 pistols to choose from. No crossbows or black powder guns which are very popular for hunting these days. If there could be more of a variety in the game that would be great. Also it's not a survival game; no crafting, no building, no food consumption. This isn't really a problem but when you have an open outdoor world and all you do is shoot animals, buy guns and shoot more animals it gets kinda boring. Also very limited customization for your character. You can change the gender from make to female but the only thing you can change after that is the color of your camouflage jacket and pants. And you can't even see your character. Not even the arms. And the other colors besides the stock ones are expensive like 5 figure expensive. And when you can't even see it it makes no sense. What they should have done was make it so you can change your hat,boots, jacket, etc and allow a third person view to see your character. Maybe add safety harnesses and other add-ons to make your character unique. Maybe we can make some of this stuff in some kind of crafting table or something. Anyway the game is pretty fun and it's definitely worth getting but don't expect a super exciting experience. It's more relaxing than exiting and that's ok sometimes we need a break from the action and take things slow once in awhile. So that's my review thanks for reading and I'll see you guys next time bye bye!"
,Recommended,518790,34118097,Posted: 8 August,all,mastermime,"The hunter call of the wild is a very addicting game in my oppinion because of the difficulty range of hunting different animals and the different tactics required to hunt different animals. Granted the hunting isn`t really entirely difficult but its difficult enough so you have to pay attention to what your doing and the mechanics make you feel like your a real hunter and you are using quite a bit of skill to track your prey and go undetected and spot them then finally shoot that animal you have been tracking down. Its also satisfying to ""claim your trophy"" in this game and look at where your shots hit and what part of the animal the shots damaged and then read out the statistics of the animal you killed. This is a game that to me would be boring on first sight because Im more into playing as another animal species than a human although the hunter call of the wild is one of a select few games were you play as a human that even I like. Its also a relaxing game to me because of the calm peaceful wilderness to look at and the sounds of nature. In my oppinion I definitely recomend this game to people who like to relax and play an addictive peacful game and to people who want a realistic hunting sim."
