,Not Recommended,518790,30438561,Posted: 10 March,all,TheDutchCoder,"TL;DR; Disappointing bugs and instability, but promising game.Let me start off by saying I've played the original theHunter A LOT, before it became the pay-to-play/win disaster that it is now. I played the original right when the game was released and only had one reserve, so I'm very familiar with the basics of the game and the team behind it.That being said, I saw this game being reviewed and was fairly excited as it looked good and seemed to have taken a more mature turn.However, the game in its current state has quite a large amount of bugs that (in my opinion) prevent me from having a fun experience. My main issue is that a lot of these bugs are super simple things that are obvious right from the start, so I'm surprised this hasn't been caught by QA,For example: map marker will never show up in the location you try to put them in. I'm fairly sure this is tied to the fact that the engine doesn't have proper widescreen support (like the original) and scales the UI improperly (circles are ovals for me). Also, if you do place a marker, 100% of the time the marker will not show up currectly in the game until you reset the marker and add it again. Something that's incredibly annoying and it's a mystery how such an obvious issue has not been addressed.Furthermore, the ""tutorial"" part is... a little bugged? I didn't find any tracks at all, until I was a good mile into a random direction, even though the lady announced ""there's a track nearby"". I've seen the same happening in a YouTube review of the game, so I'm not alone.There's also voice lines in the wrong order, which is confusing at best.My game also crashed a few times while playing (I refunded the game, so I haven't played really more than 2 hours), which to me is a show stopper. You simply can't release a crashing game in my opinion, and I'm also not the only one for whom this happens.Either way, I can totally see this game being great for some people already that might not have these issues and I'm more than willing to give it another shot in the future after patches are in place, but unfortunately my experience has been very bad so far and can not recommend this game."
