,Recommended,518790,30782461,Posted: 27 March,all,TRIPPIST,"Ok, so first of all, i want to state that it is very hard for me to post a review about this game.  The reason being that i have so much to say about it, making it hard to put it all together or organize it into one conclusive review on the game.  I may review this review multiple times and change or add things to it.Moving on to the actual review i would like to say, being a hunter in reality, that this game is trying its best to meet my expectations for a realistic, interactive hunting game. The graphics are absolutely incredible, I can walk almost anywhere on the reserve and either admire the view of far off areas, or simply enjoy the placement of the brush and trees in my immediate vacinity.  I admire this game for its graphic attention to detail.The graphics are not the only thing i admire, as they do not make or break a game.  The gameplay and game mechanics are impressive as well.  The pause menu in the game impresses me for several reasons. I enjoy the design of the map and how the waypoint placement works (although a problem with previous waypoints interfering with current ones until removed is slightly annoying), the map works well and i like the ability to fast travel between discovered cabins. I enjoy the fact that missions are implemented but not essential.  I enjoy that the devs focused on both main styles of hunting, ambushing and stalking, and the available skills for both styles. I enjoy that with certain skills you actually have to activate them to use them, and that some have a cool down time. Personally i think it makes it more challenging, and makes you think more.Moving on to the animals in the game... I like the fact that different animals react differently than others.  Not all animals react the same to sight, smell, and sound as others.  Implimenting those differences is attention to detail that i appreciate as a gamer and a hunter.  The only constructive criticizm i can give, is that i hope they plan to add a massive about of different species including different game sizes. An example being multiple small game type animals having their own scoring.Moving to maps... I truly enjoy the detail put into developing both of the maps.  They are both huge and there are so many different areas to explore and new sights to see.  I have no complaints about the maps that already exist.  The only thing i coult hope for is that they add several more, just as intricate maps, from all over the world with scores of different species for each area.Overall i think this game is amazing.  It is the game i have been waitng for since Big Game Hunter.  The ""Perfect"" hunting game.  Although they are onto an amazing start, i think there is always so much more they can add to eventually make this the most amazing hunting experience available without actually going into the woods with a gun.  If i had to add one suggestion to the game... It would be this...I think it would be an amazing idea to add a trophy room to the game.  It should be a building you have to find in each region.  When you locate this ""trophy room"", and claim it, it should display a spot on the wall for each species in the area.  Each space should contain a mount of the largest scoring animal you have harvested of that species.  Along with a list of every other animal you have harvested in that species. Every time you harvest a bigger scoring animal of that species, the wall mount should be replaced with that animal.This game is amazing.  Overall i have no complaints.  I look forward to seeing where this game goes and i am sure that i will enjoy it regardless."
