76561198144603356,Recommended,518790,31790254,Posted: 16 May,all,shannon.clemans,"This sim is merely potential... It is missing A LOT of fundemental gameplay elements to really be considered a respectable hunting sim. The graphics are amazing as far as environmental quality and yes, the maps are sufficient in size, but there is no ethics system...  I don't like hunting games that suggest that players just kill everything in sight. In most cases, real world hunting is mired heavily in rules and regulations. To really get a respectable real world account of things, there must be a licensing system... season system... area code so as to ba allowed to hunt in your designated area etc..further more it should incude field dressing, more extensive weapon and gear set up... like scope mounts that allow use of sights via high mount, see through rings. Picatinny rail mounts and quick release, Bipods and bipod sticks,  rain gaurds, glare gaurds, butt stock ammo carriers (players should only be allowed to carry as much as they could in real life) slings, workbenches and tools. That brings me to my next subject. Game needs to include gun maintenence such as cleaning and bore sighting. It would also be soooo much more immersive if you'd incude vehicles and camping gear-tents for rest and save points, campfres and cooking and all other types of survival gameplay. Also, more complete subsumption system for game (animal) NPC. I recomend only because its a good foundation but needs a lot of work."
