76561198031126820,Recommended,518790,32344858,Posted: 11 June,all,Mooncatt,"Well, what can i say about this game. im gonna start with how well my pc runs it.I run an i5 devils canyon cpu OC to 4.8ghz, GTX 770 card and 16gb corsair vengeance RAM.I can't run this game on max settings, my card is too old lol. But i have been a little unhappy with the graphics on this game, i.e when moving, they graphics are VERY grainy. when motionless its awesome. ive also seen a lot of people complain about this too. A solution to this is to use a 3rd party program which ive heard helps. I didnt want to do this as i feel i shouldnt need to. I messed about for ages with the settings trying to find another solution....i found one. I play on a 42"" sony bravia tv (1080p) no amount of graphics changing got rid of the problem, until i changed my TV settings and lowered the sharpness. problem pretty much solved.Anyway, back to the game. well not to put too finer point on it its bloody amazing. The immersion, the gameplay are all totally unreal! I hunt in real life and this is what im comparing it to.There are missions and also side missions to complete for extra XP and creds. they start off pretty easy but they do get really hard. e.g shoot a red fox with a bow....sounds easy right? not when you cant see the bleeding things in the first place coz they like dense foliage! not to mention the fact that the range of the bow is shorter than jimmy cranky! another 2 spring to mind. harvest a white tail deer at over 150m...again sounds east....not when there is a whole amazon rain forest in you way!. the last one is take a photo (and there are a few ""take a photo mission"") of two bears, hard when you only ever see one on their own. But, these are ""challenges"" for a reason! and they give the game some longevity along with the massive XP needes at over level 15 to level up or aquire perk points.I would like to point out that to people new to hunting... of any kind... that this is not a game you can play just for half an hour! it takes time.....and a lot of it! ive played now for about 55 hours and im still no where near opening up even one reserve! I think a lot of people that dont know how to hunt or are new to it are gonna find this game very frustrating. for e.g...there is a lot of dense forest and foliage. hunting like this is hard, but as i discovered there are a lot of open fields and lakes to find and this is where to hunt.the bad points...Like any game there are bugs, and im sorry to say there are quite a few of them in this one. But the game is relatively new and the Devs are releasing patches all the time. here is what ive found...sometimes you hit an animal and it leaves no blood trail or any tracks (new to me as of the last patch)sometimes you hit an animal and despite the vital wound and huge blood loss rate it never diessometimes you will hear an animal call and there will be no direction indicator.sometimes your weapons will vanish from your hands and cant get them back (fix...go into inventory and swap your weapon to a new slot and back again....problem solved)The user interface isnt too friendly, it takes a while to learn how to equip rounds and scopes etc i cant understand why bullets that are bought are not automatically added.I also dont like the map. most of the time when you pull the map up its zoomed in on the out edges of the map....why cant it automatically be centered on your position?there are prolly other things i cant think of off the top of my head as i write this.There are a variety of weapons in the game from hand guns, rifles, shotguns and bows. There are also 2 different rounds for each rifle (not sure about the shotguns as i dont use them that often) but in reality there are sooo many more varieties of rounds and i wish they would put this in the game too. As you start the game you are given a .243 which in all honesty is all you will ever need...until you start coming across bison and bears. the .243 will kill them but you are going to be tracking your animal for quite a while until it bleeds out. the next rifle is the .270 which will put down pretty much most things. im currently using the 7mm and its good enough for anything, i see other people on youtube using the .338 rangemaster buts its very expensive and when looking at the stats it isnt that much better than the 7mm. actually when i think about it? there isnt a big enough gulf between the rifles to warrant spending huge amounts of in game moneyto buy anything above the 7mm...even the .270 is good enough.so my conclusion....the game needs work but as it stands it is very very good. It needs more rifles and bullet variations and the in game graphics (grainy stuff) needs eliminating. the perks and skill tree also needs work, some of the perks you will never need. e.g the bullets tend not to be affected by wind (from what i can see) etc but there is a perk that shows you wind direction and speed (not for you own scent, this is built in already on the compass)  there is another one for weather too...again i see no real reason to have this because the games in built weather isnt severe enough to warrant having this skill at all. There are other things i might mention but id be nit-picking.so if i had not bought this yet, would i buy? hell yes. despite the few niggles overall its a fantastic game and a must have for any hunter enthusiast. I really hope they add more reserves to hunt and more weapons and bullet variations.90/100"
