life not killing anything is still entertaining, doing it in a game is lame and no one would play that.  The graphics are not ground breaking but the lighting, effects, and scale of things make it seem more polished than it probably is (its pleasant walking through the forrest).  As far as the hunter classic went I thought that was a garbage game, I thought it looked like trash, played about the same, and the pay model was a complete rip off.  This game on the other hand is worth the asking price as long as they fix what is above.  Not that it has much competition but it quickly became my favorite hunting game.THE MEH - The sound, no surround option, why WHY!?  Random light glitchyness and mildly annoying bugs.  The menus, specifically the loadout/store menu is really unpolished.  It also wont save my settings.THE I WISH - I wish there was a visual difference in the animal racks, not just small and big along with an arbitrary ""trophy score"" once you harvest the animal.  I wish there was 4wheelers.  I wish small game hunting mattered (cannot harvest upon killing/no XP).  I wish guns were more true to life with their penetration instead of the arcady ""weapon balance"" to make different calibers arbitrarily matter.  I wish there was a hardcore mode so the sim guys could get their fix along with much more of a challenge.  I wish there was waterfowl hunting... and upland birds... and hunting dogs, please give us some quail and grouse."
