,Recommended,518790,31680878,Posted: 11 May,all,lakku,"This game in my opinion is really underrated. Here's my quick review and summary also after 22 hours of gameplay without complaining about one freaking DLC that seems to be 90% of the reviews.Get this game if you want:- Something peaceful- Challenge- Peace of mind- Exciting moments- Immerse yourselfDon't buy this game if you don't have/or want:- Patience- Run & gun- Don't like simulators- Can't afford 4€ for a DLCMy review below:Years ago I tested theHunter - free to play game. I didn't like it, I was younger & playing totally different games. Now that simulators and games that require patience are mostly the games I play, I'm in love with this. First day I bought this I played freaking 12 hours straight, I haven't played a game that long when I was a teenager.theHunter - Call of the Wild is a steal at this price in my opinion. The visuals & landscape is stunning and immersive. I had no problem running this game around 100 FPS @ Ultra. No stuttering, quick loads and 0 crashes. I'm stunned that there's even a game like this out. Audio design, holy hell, it's perfect. Hearing the thunder roar startled me for the first time, rain fall from the sky and all the sounds of the forest. It is absolutely the best sound design I've heard in years. Everything ranging from weather, guns to animals.Gameplay is simple to learn but some elements such as sneaking and being the perfect stalker & ambusher is hard to master. It's mostly about trial and error. There are some elements I really MISS such as free look (please, give me a reason to press Alt). Gunplay is a disappointment though, what this game needs is proper zeroing. Having to adjust your scope & sights with just a simple Pg Up or Pg Down button would be great. I know there's a skill for it but it only gives two ranges, short & long. This really in my opinion makes the rangefinder useless. I hope in the future patches they improve upon this.AI of the animals is pretty 50/50 at this point. They sometimes (really rare) get stuck on the rocks and become an easy kill at this point. If you kill at one area, the animals will avoid it, I don't know how long the timer is but it's usually marked with purple color on the map. I've had a spot for two days where I killed 4 fallow deers and I haven't seen any animals anymore around the area. They avoid it like a plague. Aggressive animals are sometimes pretty confusing such as the european bison, surely it would attack or be more aggressive towards you if they notice you & you shoot them. The AI needs to be MORE dangerous!Content itself, if you buy this game, what will you do? You can do the story & side missions. You can even disable them if you just want to hunt, progress on levels & skills and unlock new weapons. Love photography? You can take AMAZING screenshots in this game. This game is more for mature audience than your average mainstream gamer. Try to find the rarest animals, albinos, get best scores or medals on kills. This game is pure trophy hunting and improving your skills. Trial and error. Don't lose your patience, it took me a whole day just to do the mission where you have to kill a red fox with a bow. It felt so good when I got the shot.Few things that annoyed me though in the beginning were the skill trees and the perks. Some of the skills & perks are so obvious in hunting that they should be on first tiers or at tier 0. The tiers atm are kinda messed up imo, they could look into this and fix them.A quick note about the multiplayer. Me and my friend tried it. There's no desync problems or anything, it works smooth, you can hop in and out easily. There was something wrong though that the user interface started bugging for both of us. Stucked messages that only occurred in multiplayer. At this point, I really don't have an opinion about the multiplayer side of this game. Mostly I could not see myself playing this game with anyone else though, it's my own zen simulator. Hunting has always fascinated me and the patience it needs. I think I have found a new gaming genre which also to follow along with milsims & survival games.Future hopes that the devs will actually do:- More maps- More animals- More guns (give me a Mosin Nagant!!)- Winter landscape- Desert landscape? Would be interesting!Rating: 8.0/10Good job developers! Keep on improving the game and adding more content.PS EDIT before someone loses their♥♥♥♥♥♥and starts giving me threats:Yeah I know, the fuss about the DLC is that it's a good feature and should have been a free update or a main feature in the game before release. What can you do? A one DLC doesn't ruin a good game and one mistake.NOTE: I have encountered only a handful bugs, people say that this game is buggy. Where are all my crashes & bugs man?"
