76561197970876127,Recommended,518790,31526775,Posted: 3 May,all,Pig...In...Space!!,"<h1>The ultimate hiking simulator (with guns)</h1>When the wind blows over the lakes, you shiver behind your keyboard, when the sun breaks through on that perfect Indian summer day, you feel the warmth on your skin. The ambient sounds of the forest match real life one to one. Hiking through the reserves is a deeply relaxing experience. The animal animations are nice and the particle system is very pleasing.The actual hunt is inexplicably exciting. I caught myself jerking the mouse as one would overexcited jerk the trigger and miss the target because of it....The developers have made a huge open world immersive experience and for that, they have my respect.<b>The game is a “must have” if you enjoy beautiful landscapes and killing fury animals.</b><i>About bugs:</i>Yes, the game has bugs. After each patch there are noticeably less of them. I'm particularly impressed by the performance improvement of the particle system. That must have been a hard one.Did the bugs take the joy out of the game? Absolutely not. Still great.I'm confident they'll also fix the remaining bugs.<i>About the price:</i>I played the game over 150 hours and I'm still enjoying it. So, is 30 euro a fair price? Totally.Don't forget that the average AAA game costs over 50 euro and contains less then 30 hours of game play, for example the Half Life series, South Park: the stick of truth and the Portal series. I'd buy all those games again, even with those unfavourable play time to cost ratios.The Hunter COTW is a niche game. Killing digital deer is an acquired taste (at best). It will never sell like GTA or HALO. It takes a lot of balls for a game studio to reach for AAA quality in such a small market.So at 20 cents per hour, instead of 2 euro per hour, it's the best damn deal I've made on Steam to date.<i>About paid DLC:</i>They'd have to. It costs millions to make a game like COTW and at 30 euro per game, in the afore mentioned small market, it'd be very hard to break even. It certainly would be impossible to add new content like reserves or game play assets like Tents & Blinds.I applaud this little Swedish game studio and their brave endeavour to bring us a beautiful world for all beings without fur!"
