76561198033720036,Recommended,518790,29966139,Posted: 16 February,all,Jason,"A great improvement on TheHunter Classic. The graphics are better, the sounds are better, the environment is better, and the animals are better - especially the rabbits hiding in the underbrush. It's just better. There are also visible trails of bent grass where the animal you're tracking travelled, which is awesome and makes tracking much more intuitive than the search patterns you probably learned to do in theHunter Classic, and the render distance isn't capped. That's right you can shoot out beyond 200 meters now - there's even a 400m kill achievement!At release the menus are pretty clunky, but you can work with them. I haven't experienced any major bugs except having to switch to the map screen to exit a menu. Once they patch it up this will be a solid title.If you're a stalker-type hunter, like me, you'll probably want to know that if you use a controller with analog sticks there is a range of movement speeds that will allow you to move while walking and crouching without alarming nearby animals. If you use a M+K setup only the WASD keys have you moving at maximum speed and you'll alarm the animals even when crouching. I use an Xbox One controller to stalk then switch to my M+K to shoot because aiming with a controller is way too hard. Hopefully the devs add a movement speed toggle for M+K, but until they do stalking is really only possible with a controller."
