76561198058307519,Recommended,518790,31434563,Posted: 29 April,all,OG Cpt. BongDoritos,"Alright so this is as honest as I can get, and this does not include the dlc I haven't played the dlc and from what I understand I probably won't.I would appreciate it if you don't mind sticking it out til the end as it's both the good and bad.I recommend this game as it's very fun, beautiful, very realistic, and overall worth the 30 dollars I spent.People complain about the bugs left and right, none of which that i have found to date are anything more than a annoyance, such as the occasional deer running into a tree and being unkillable. None of the bugs I have found or experianced would make me refund or take back my experiances in this game.Now the first thing I want to say is this game isn't for people who just want to get in and kill stuff, it doesn't work like that in the slightliest. First animal I killed outside of the tutorial was a Fallow deer that took me 1 shot to it's upper chest, hitting 1 lung and about 5-8 minutes or running after his blood trial to find him laying down in the dirt claimed him etc. I kiled deer for a while until I managed to be able to buy a bow, being somone who prefers a bow in real life I thought this would be awesome. I was semi-dissapointed out when I figured out it was god awful and the wind in the game is always to harsh to be able to shoot an accurate shot at anything over 20 meters probably, even then it might be shetchy at best.So after going back to my original gun for a while I managed to save up enough for some other stuff new ammo etc, tbh doesn't help much but slightly easier to kill stuff. I really didn't get any return on investment as I started hunting red deer which took 2-3 shoots it seems to kill and accounting for misses. So go back to default ammo because yeah.. Save up enough for the first sidearm (.343 magnum I believe) This I took this thing isn't the second reservation as that's where I was for a while because it's better money and the game isn't that much harder to kill for the most part. Again to my dissapointment this magnum was virtually useless as when I went up against a bear that ended up rushing me after I made him mad took all 6 shots, plus 2 from my rifle before he went down, to give it some credit i did manage one time to sneak up on a whitetale and shoot it straight through the side... to say the least it bleed out in seconds, but honestly wasted more of my money. So basically only stick with rifles, I haven't tried shotguns but I'm assuming they aren't better.Alright now heres where the real bitterness of my gameplay has happened, while yes I am using the first gun, with default bullets. It is absolutely redic how long killing some animals can take, I went up against a female moose and shot it through both lungs on my first shot, shot it in the hind leg, upper left shoulder blade, after nearly 30 minutes of tracking this thing with a low blood loss rate I get it into a feild and out of breathe I take a shot and hit it in the back of the leg and it drops head... How did it survive 3 shots the first being through both lungs, run for a literal 30 minutes. Coming from a family of hunters even though it's a .243 should be able to take down a moose relatively fast if you shoot it through both lungs, a hindleg, and a shoulder blade... if it's not dead it certainly shouldn't be able to full blown spring, more then less move...Now I'm sure you're out here thinking okay, well why didn't you just buy a better rilfe? Well jokes on me apparently that there is the cost of the rifle, 12,000. And then you have to have a rifle skill of 743 (I believe) and you only get 15 or so from killing a deer if you perfectly 1 shot it with a heart shot, or something good like that. If you get it with a poor shot, persay in the spine it's about 10 or so. If it's a shot through the stomache and it bleeds to death it's like 5. (Moose and bear are about 30 if you land a 1 shot 1 kill) So it takes you lots of killing to get, I had about 40,000 (spent/saved) when I was finally able to obtain a better rifle. So overall the skill point portion of buying stuff is way to outrageous. Even with the better rifle it's not very good, it's solid enough to consistently 1 shot most deer (being a .270 I hope it would) if you get a good hit, but still isn't anything good enough for killing moose, elk, bear, bison which is semi expected but I would still assume it's good enough to take them out after hitting them twice in prime locations which it isn't. I must also not suggest hunting bear, or elk, or moose with the beginning rifle as it has taken me 8 shots to kill a bear from bleeding before.The sway on the gun is pretty heavy. And as far as your breath goes it's absolutely awful if you don't have any upgrades for it. Like seriously it must be a 70 year old man who has been smoking 2 packs a day since he was 11. At max (un-upgraded) you can only hold your breathe for about 4 seconds. Realistically you can hold your breath for about 10-15 in while hunting. But it's not to bad, even if it's only 4 seconds.But the game is really good, very realistic with the expection of some of those 300000000 bullets, and 17 hours of tracking kills that happen every now and again. The shooting in the game takes some time to get used to it's not a shooter game in the slightest. The scenery ins absolutely amazing especially on maxed out graphics. The sun being able to be seen through the trees with beams of light and you know the whole deal. If a cloud is above you the sun goes out in your direct area. Fog is very nice. Rain is great (does rain to much honestly but w/e). The sounds of the wind alone make the game immersive.If you're wanting a game that can be about as realistic as it can get without going out and hunting your self. This is the game for now. There hasn't been any games I've seen/heard of that compare. If this game was somehow made into VR and done properly, I imagine this game would be absolutely amazing.  It's also a good game with friends, though the multi-player is glitchy and has it's problems again nothing game breaking. If you want a game that is relaxing and entertaining enough to play while you're trying to un-tilt from a game of league where your team intentionally feeds this could be it."
