76561198260017570,Recommended,518790,32868015,Posted: 27 June,all,djb204,"This is one of the best hunting games I ever played, but..... there are some issues. If you are willing to overlook them, then this game is for you. As for the issues...- Bow hunting can be very frustrating. The wind had such an extreme effect on the arrow, it's rediculous. This could be fixed eventually, but currently most people avoid the bows all together.I'm a controller user so...- Controller support? Hardly. Sure you can play the game with a controller to a degree, but there are some issues that WILL effect gameplay. One major issue is they have mapped the (holding breath) button to the same analog stick that makes your character move/walk. Trying to hold your breath for a shot only to ACCIDENTLY start walking and causing your scope to sway all over is rage worthy. What's worse is they offer no button remapping, so you either put up or shut up. Another issues is the crouch button is the same as the stand up button and it's bugged. Numorous times I've tried to conceal my position from an approaching animal only to immediately stand back up. It's happens if your crouched to and try to stand, your character would automatically revert back to the previous stance position. (button remapping? non-existent). Driving the ATV with a controller might seem like the way to go, but unlike mouse/KB, there is an auto center camera on controllers that limits the ability to look around while driving around. There are other controller bugs that can be found in the bug report section of the forums, but these are some of the more pressing bugs.I'm sure these bugs will be worked out eventually, but they have other bugs that take priority position. I keep coming back after every patch to read the patch notes, but controller support just isn't a top priority."
