,Recommended,518790,31456343,Posted: 29 April,all,sirdraco9876,"From playing just under two hours this game gives a good impression and appears to be a more realistic and more serious game than the Cabella's games, without hiding everything behind a pay wall. This is what theHunter should have been.Graphically this game is beautiful. The way the light and the shadows look just make it so impressive and almost gives the impression of actually being there, and it makes you want to wander around. And the desire to explore is something you want in a hunting game right?The game play is different enough from theHunter to make it truely feel like its own game. It has a ""Quest"" system in the game which reward the player with currency. I got over 5000 within the time I played, which seems decent. They also reward the player with equipment, for example one of the missions gave me a Predator ""Jackrabbit"" call, which attracts Foxes and other animals who prey one rabbits. The only drawback is that everything in the store seems to be really expensive, but it rewards those who are better hunters.They introduced a new system which makes animals clear out of a area where there was a gunshot recently. This helps avoid the broken AI that is sometimes seen in theHunter Classic. They also made a system where the animals have a need they must fufill during certain parts of the day. This is extremely helpfun and would allow a great hunter to kill multiple animals at a time.They also added a skill system which is a massive improvement from the base game. This affects many aspects of the game, from weather to tracking to lures.This improves the game massively and makes hunting faster, funner, and eaiser.All in all, I have to say this is a excellent game and its very fun, however I do not feel that it jusifies a $30 dollar price tag. This would be something to pick up on sale or on a rainy day.Most people have a issue with the ""Tents and Ground Blinds"" dlc which seems overpriced because it adds something that should have been free and it adds a whole whopping two items for four dollars. I dont think its overpriced because both items seem useful, and they can be taken down and rebuilt anywhere. The Tents act like a fast travel beacon and the blinds help hide you while giving great sight lines around it. I just hope they dont add more tents and blinds dlc's, but instead add more to the dlc."
