76561198136587450,Recommended,518790,30406163,Posted: 9 March,all,Eilif,"I was a little nervous getting this game, as many reports problems with game crash, lag and freeze. Guess i am a lucky one, as i never encountered this at all. It really runs smoothly even on the highest settings. I run the game on an MSI Intel i7-4720HQ, 16GB RAM, NVIDIA GTX960.This is the most beautiful game i ever played where you walk in an astonishing surroundings. You just cant help but stop frequently to enjoy the view. The animals also looks good with nice animation. If i should put my finger on anything, the lake / ponds could maybe have a better texture.The sounds are good and with no problems to hear where they coming from. But at some random events, some of the sounds dissappear or turns in to noise. Not the best thing when using earplugs.You have the option to start in two different maps, Central European and North-west American. Both maps are huge with so many places to explore, you could easily play for houndreds of hours before you been on all the places.The animals however, seems to need more work. As it is now, there are some issues. An animal trying to run away from you, can end up being stuck if a tree or rock stands in their path. I also seen animals getting stuck in a loop, such as an animal chance direction when hitting tree A, and turns towards tree B, so it chance direction to tree A again and therefor chance direction again to tree B. In the tutorial, they tell us about hunting pressure and animals would avoid areas where you just killed. This isnt true at all. Animals doesnt seem to care about this for a second and would gladly walk in to an area and stand besides their fellow mates who just got shot. There are a dozen number of animals to hunt, and some of them is to be expected to attack you in defence. But if i stand only 6-7 meters away from a black bear or big moose and shoot but only get a flesh hit, i am still not attacked. The only time i got injured from an animal was when standing at its running-away path, and was runned over. And since animals are running away from you, not towards you, this is obviously not something you need to worry happen often.I have also come across animals who just stands there frozen. This is at night, so i guess they are sleeping. But if i shoot them without getting instant kill, they just run 2-3 steps before they stop and freeze again. It looks very weird.One thing i noticed first time i played this was how slow i walk. Its realistic, as you are hunting and wouldnt like to make noise. So crouching should be slow moving. But normal walking are just as well slow and walking up the stairs to a watch tower reminded me of walking with my grandmother. So it all ends up with me running around. Thats actually not so bad. Its extremly noisy and scares animals around you. In this way i can find out if there is any animals around me at all and if there is, where they are from their warning calls.The game have a nice earn money and skill system making you work to improve and afford better equipment.All in all, this is a game i enjoy and would keep playing. You need a little patient, just like in real life. But is nice and relaxing game to play when you have no time pressure upon you. The only downside for me is the animal behaviour and running path that needs an improvement. This is not an alpha game, so i am not shure it will ever be fixed."
,Recommended,518790,30424925,Posted: 10 March,all,lucianoip,"After 50 hours of gameplay I can make a review not based on emotion.TLDR: If you like hunting games, or want a different experience from the action games / FPS, buy it!Graphics:The game is beautiful. Landscapes are gorgeous. Lighting is awesome. Wind is awesome, leaves flying with the direction and strenght of the wind...animals are beautiful too...Everything about graphics are great in this game. I've been playing video games for 30 years and this is the first time I really enjoy not doing anything but looking around.My PC is not high end (i5 4460, 8GB, GTX 970) and I can play with good FPS on high, average on ultra.Gameplay:The game is hard. At least until you understand what is a hunting game, you'll probably get frustated. You will have hard time finding anything to shoot. And if you find, you'll ending doing a poor shot, because of the physics (they re very good).And the game is slow. Not the movements and stuff, but hunting is a slow down experience...You cant go running all around.So if you want a different experience from high speed FPS like Overwatch, CoD, BF, etc, this is a good game for you.I'm really enjoying it. A lot. I see me playing this for like 1000 hours at least (if the game receive updates for more content). With the actual content, I guess I'll have like 100-200 hours of fun, because is kinda hard to get exp and money."
,Recommended,518790,30424935,Posted: 10 March,all,pleX,"Not quite a hunting simulation, but very fun. Aesthetically, the game is gorgeous. The dense vegetation, sun rays, shadows and textures make for a very immersive experience. The sound is done very well, although I wish there was a slider for certain sound effects like rain, which can get quite loud.Gameplay-wise, the game is good, but not fantastic yet. The ui and certain features and menus seem quite rushed. The animal and their behavior is overall pretty solid, but I am disappointed there isn't a deep truRACs feature like the original thehunter where trophies were unique and all the animals were different. With this system, you simply have a ""trophy score"" added to get your final overall score after a harvest.The game is more arcadey than the previous thehunter (called classic now) There are many more animals, the score system is not as refined and deep, but it makes for a good game you can pick up and play for about 30 minutes and still have a successful hunt.The game does suffer from several technical bugs and crashes and should have been released as an early access game, but once the kinks are ironed out I think this game can be great. So far the early patches have been excellent in this regard. I recommend this to anyone who is a fan of hunting, but also to anyone who simply wants to be immersed and experience the thrill of hunting and tracking.  I recommend having a very solid gaming PC, however, because in my opinion the biggest draw to this game is being immersed in the large maps and vegetation, so if you don't have a great PC and would have to run it on low settings I couldn't recommend it."
