,Recommended,518790,30602861,Posted: 18 March,all,Mai7Viac,"Just a couple thoughts on this game. First, this is probably one of the best hunting games out right now, it feels like there's been a dry spell for these over the past few years. Understandable since it's a small fan base I'm sure. Nonetheless, this game is quite fun and enjoyable to play solo. A couple thoughts after putting in 12-15ish hours:- The game is quite slow paced, I saw a joke of ""walking simulator 2017"" and it's not far off. I'd love to see an ATV or the ability to fast travel to blinds/stands/lookouts.- This one time, I shot a doe in the head and it ran away. When I eventually tracked it down the shot tracker basically showed the bullet going right into the center of the skull and said ""flesh, skull, jaw"" So yeah...that happens- Personally, I think putting guns behind a level-up wall is BS. At least give me some other options.- Also, I have yet in my life to see a single-shot 7mm Magnum that someone actually takes hunting.- More guns plz. Seriously, there's like 9 rifles.- The stealth system could use a little more balance. For example: I want two speeds of crouch walking (toggle crouch, hold shift to move a little faster). Then walking should not producer the same amount of sound as running. You can walk quite softly through the woods IRL- The UX is strange. It took me 10 minutes to figure out that items in the store scroll left to right- Speaking of store, the text on the guns and stuff moves really fast, be nice if the space for the text was a little bigger so it didn't have to scroll.Please don't take my critisism to mean it's a bad game. It's not at all. In fact I've quite enjoyed the few hours I've put in. I hope it gets some updates and changes in the future. Definetly recommend if you're into the whole hunting genre."
