76561198032088713,Recommended,518790,30915537,Posted: 2 April,all,Gabriel Yu Law,"I've been having fun with this game for a little over two weeks. I like it a lot and would recommend it.I'll just give you some pros and cons rather than some tl;dr in depth review.PROS:Beautiful enviroment with immersive weather and day night cyclesAccurate, and immersive sounds from the environment and surrounding animalsDecently Realistic animal behaviors and senses, including smell sight and sound awareness.Option to vary the degree of realism (offers the choice of toggling various visual assistance effects)Landmarks and Lore points throughout the map add depth and interesting information.Good weapon mechanicsFairly indepth tutorialGood choice of weaponsAwesome X-ray view breakdown of kills to show shot placement and anatomy effectedEuropean and American Pacific Hunting worlds availableMaps are EXPANSIVE. Lots of places to go.Multiplayer CapableActive Dev team making corrections oftenCons:Honestly, the only real con I can think of that isn't just a subjective opinion  would be the Bugs.There are several bugs, the most of these occur in multiplayer. Nothing gamebreaking per se, but some that can be quite irritating.(I would personally like there to be even more types of animals to hunt, ie, Rams, Caribou, Grizzlies, Turkeys, more species of deer)Quick Bug list and frequency of occurrence as of 4/2/2017:1) Animal AI not initiating properly leading to helpless game standing still. (Occasionally in both SP And MP) (in 2 weeks of playing, iv'e seen it 4 times)2) Animal Entity State failing to update properly, leading to animals running in place after being shot, and then being non-harvestable after being killed.   (In MP, Occurs Frequently (~30% of kills)  *NEVER occurs in SP.* ---Possible Netcode issue)3) Deer Bleat call can be heard loudly by the player when being used by any other players on the map, regardless of location or distance in world. (Always/100% bug rate. MP bug only)4) Animals Struck by Player weapon leaving no tracks or blood trails whatsoever. (Rarely happens on both MP and SP) (Happened twice in 45 hrs of playtime once each on MP and SP modes)5) Certain Animal call lures will glitch when you crouch while they are triggering their animation/sound file, causing the player to be unable to use the caller again until after switching between active items. (100% with certain callers both MP and SP) --minor irritation.6) Tritium (glowdot) iron sights auto-unequiping from rifle when switching between items. (100% MP and SP)7) Scope sights removed from backpack and left in storage still equipable. (100% SP & MP)"
