76561198233152980,Recommended,518790,30204652,Posted: 26 February,all,Sackhead,great gamegraphics  is insane one of the bestso many animals and easier to track than the last Thehunterleveling up is amazing and perksgood fpsa must buy
,Recommended,518790,30203512,Posted: 26 February,all,Toumal,"Soooooo, this game. It looks damn amazing. The controls are solid and the aiming, shooting, etc. are competently done. But the reviews are mixed, so what gives?The big problem this game has at the moment is issues with animals getting stuck in terrain and you getting killed if you get stick in a little ditch in the ground.There's other issues too, for example I'm missing a decent form of transporation in the extremely vast maps. Yes there's teleport to outposts you discovered before, but getting there can sometimes take a very long time.Where's my Bullet cam? I know it's not realistic, but I loved having good shots rewarded with a satisfying Sniper-esque slowmo bullet-following camera. Sadly this game doesn't have this at all, not even as an option.Unlocking the various items can take a bit of time, with some of the objectives really testing your patience.The bugs are the major negative as far as I can see. The game is gorgeous though, the two environments are well crafted and positively massive in size. The sound design is a 9/10 with some individual sounds sticking out from the mix more than they should, but overall it's a beautiful experience to roam through the forest in this game. Some of ambient bird calls aren't exactly correct for a supposedly german forest, but I'm nitpicking here. The weapon sounds are realistic and satisfying.You only get two maps though, as well as a handful of weapons. The animal variety also isn't too great. However it's only 30 Euros at the time of writing, and the devs were smart enough to provide a skill and perk system to help with long term motivation. If you're a fan of hunting games, or enjoy realistic renditions of nature in games, this is a solid game. No microtransactions, what you see is what you get.Could do with bugfixing though. The issues don't happen all the time, but they're there.Overall, considering the price and the quality of the environments, and the otherwise solid shooting mechanics, I give this one a thumbs up."
,Recommended,518790,30213134,Posted: 26 February,all,ThtCooperFellow,"I don't really have much to say that is negative. Be prepared to walk. A lot. No, I mean a LOT. Luckily, I'm rather enjoying the strolls when the world looks as good as it does. Sound design is pretty fantastic. My only issue is that rabbits sometimes sound like they're a bear coming through the bushes to kill me.Other than that, I've yet to encounter a real bug but I have had one CTD on startup. Again, only 4 hours so far.That said, I'm iffy on whether or not to recommend this for anyone not super interested in playing a game about hunting. Sure, you don't have to sit in a blind nearly as long as you would IRL, but you will find yourself becoming impatient if moving slowly and being mindful of the wind isn't your thing.I would hope there are some additional ways to squeeze performance out of this game, but I'm lagging behind with a GTX 770 at this point, so I've got nothing really to complain about there.My only peeve is the UI. I find it somewhat cumbersome and the menus dont seem to flow fantastically. Beyond that, not having a way to quickly switch my ammo type without having to jump into the menu is slightly aggravating.All in all however, its a pretty solid game. WAY better than that F2P nonsense with more microtransactions than almost anything I've ever seen that they made previously. The lack of those micro's means this game flows much better. If you want to go hunting from the comfort of your gaming chair, or whatever it is you sit in, this is it."
