76561198052096186,Recommended,518790,30211493,Posted: 26 February,all,BilboBaggins,"This is my first time leaving a review on Steam. Like many others I felt compelled to write a review to help others decide if this is worth a purchase in it's current state. After a considerable amount of play time, here is what I think so far! The first thing I noticed was how amazing this game looks! From lush forests to open strawfields to rocky mountains and lakes the maps provide a nice variety of scenery. The sound effects are very good and really help to immerse you in the environments. The weather system is also very good with effects like fog and cloud coverage changing lighting. The game mechanics feel good. Plenty of variety of animals. The progression system has been changed since launch making it much more accessible but somewhat challenging. Now to the ugly! This is the buggiest bugfest of a game I have ever played! Regular crashes, broken multiplayer, buggy menu icons, buggy animals, not being able to click and unlock things in the game and the list carrys on! With all that being said for me personally this game was worth the money. The developers seem to be working hard to fix issues and overall, issues aside, this has been an enjoyable experience. This game has a lot of potential."
