,Recommended,518790,33800434,Posted: 25 July,all,Magic Raptor,"This game is hard for me to review. I spent quite a bit of time on it, and I did enjoy most of the time I spent on it, but at the end of the day I feel like this game also has a lot of missed potential.Honestly, the game is buggy. It's not even a bug or two here or there; there are fundamental problems with the engine they used, where if you do something like prone on a cliffside, you literally clip through the ground and see the bottom of the map.Also, there's just a lot less gameplay in this game than I was hoping for. There's a lot of weapons, but many of them are just a grind to unlock. Weapons are straight up better than one another. There's very little reason not to use bolt-action rifles as opposed to anything else. There aren't very many animals to hunt, and a lot of them (like moose, Roosevelt elk, whitetail deer, and blacktail deer on the Layton Lakes map) behave pretty much the same; the only big differences are the distance in which they react to sound and their average herd size. This makes it very easy to ""play out"" the game like I did - there's basically a hard cap on the number of interesting things there are to do.Multiplayer is a monstrosity, with very few working features (for instance, you get nothing for any of your kills until you are in the same region as the host; it's been like this since multiplayer started working, which it basically didn't at launch, and hasn't been fixed yet) and a pretty awful community. The server browser is an absolute joke as well.But somehow, this is the pinnacle of hunting games at the moment. Most of its competitors are ridiculously arcade-y, with little replay value. The ballistics in this game are actually very impressive - different bullets drop different distances at range, for instance.Maybe I just expected something more out of this game. If you took the physics, multiplayer, and weapon selection of the original theHunter, and combined it with the graphics, increased range, and payment model of this game, you'd have a pretty ideal hunting game. And like I said at the beginning, I did enjoy the time I put into this game; it's the fact that I enjoyed the time I put into this game that leaves me wanting more. So I'm giving it a thumb's up, because I felt I got my money's worth, but I definitely think this game is a heap of lost potential."
