76561198006582789,Recommended,518790,34850345,Posted: 9 September,all,Muertington,"Really like it, but the reasons for which I like this game might not make much sense so dont mind it.If you are not patient, or just want an action packed animal shooter, dont like tracking and waiting for long times in a single spot for that perfect albino deer (rare spawn so to say) doing nothing but watching through your binoculars, if you are one of those treehuggers who think hunting is bad, if you dont like to spend literally hours trudging through woods, swamps and  forests, if the lack of a high end goal beyond annoys you (it certainly annoys me at times)...But above all the first thing mentioned: if you lack patience, do not purchase this game.Its a very inmersive (maybe not fully realistic but for realism I could buy myself a rifle and go hunting) hunting game with a rather limited variety of animals divided into two BIG hunting reserves.One in central Europe, and one in northern America (this one rocks).I think the best comparison I could do about this game is the Silent Hunter submarine simulator games.In this game you are the hunter, and you got a variety of weapons (rifles and bows substitute the submarines).Each weapon has some ammo types (torpedoes) which are more adecuated for certain situations (range, target inegrity  etc).You can freely roam the forests (seas) in search of preys, but obviously you cant just run and gun. Animals (merchants) will spot you and run away or even attack you.You have to play as a hunter (sorry for being redundant) and lay in wait submerged in the bushes or among the trees, hoping for the prey to make a pass.Or perhaps you will go into silent navigation (ehrmm I mean stealth mode) and stalk your prey to get close and personal with the bow.Or try your luck with a long range shot hoping for a kill.If you miss the shot the animal will run away, and most of the times you will have only one chance to hit him.If you aim to the weak parts (neck, head, vertebrae) it will be one shot one dead animal.Or you can hit a non vital part and then youll have to track it (sometimes for a loooong time) till you find the corpse.Over time your character will get experience points and level up, allowing you to unlock a series of perks and weapon skills that will help you further in your endeavours.There are four types of weapons: bows, rifles, shotguns and revolvers, but I have to say that the amount of weapons available in game is rather poor.You can spend your credits (earned via hunting or doing missions) in those weapons, aswell as gear such as animal attractors, backpacks, tents or some all terrain motorbike.And obviously ammo, which aint free.Right now the problem I got with the game is that there aint much to do with the credits you earn once you got the gear from the shop.Also, the variety of species aint very big (each or the two hunting reserves has its own fauna).Being a hunting game would be great to be able to set up a camp with a small fire, even if it only serves an inmersion purpose.All in all I recommend it as long as you meet the patience requirement."
