76561197990084942,Recommended,518790,35322348,Posted: 29 September,all,silverback_7,"This is a very thorough hunting simulation. I say simulation in the literal way not as a joke. Animals have (in my humble real life experience as a hunter) a very reasonable aproximation of real life behaivior. The weapons in the game reflect thier real life counterparts very well.  Twigs and dry weeds crack and snap under your feet, the rain effects your visibility and the ability for game animals to hear you. Fog is as much of a pain as you can imagine but makes for some glorious screenshots.Be warned, this is NOT a Cabelas style arcade shooter where you'll be mowing down hundreds of animals in 2 minutes with an AR-15.  Hunts for indiviual animals can last 45 minutes if you arent careful approaching and startle your target of if you dont land a lethal shot and have to track it.Your choice of weapons in this game is limited to something you might actually use on  a real hunt. Bolt action and single shot rifles are the most prevelant with shotguns and pistols alos available. Bows are also present but probably the weakest part of the game as the arrow physics arent very represetative of reality.  They are still usable but i reccommend you get used to the sneaking mechanics for close shots to assure success.For me, this is the game of a lifetime. Thorougly enjoyable because of the lack of acade style nonsense, concentrating instead on slower more authentic gameplay. Weapons and hunting equipment is realistic and is based on well known hunting tools.This game is also actively being worked on by the devs with a third reserve coming soon (as of 9/29/17) as paid DLCHighly HIGHLY recommended!!!!"
