,Recommended,518790,35309015,Posted: 29 September,all,Venezuelian militia,"Having played for over 77 hours and found most of the lookouts and camps on both maps there are a few issues that players need to understand if they want to play this game. Shooting a deer in the head from under 20m away quite often leads to low blood loss and a long run over easily ove 30 minutes before finding the body, where as hitting a deer in the neck from almost any range will result in an instant kill. While it is a good game and obviously not fast paced it can be frustrating and can put some players off easily. The kills often seem to be worked out by the software as a roll of an imaginary dice and not based on any kind of balistics or hit box. The weather is good but the down side for the player is when it rains the rain is so loud you cannot hear any animals moving around but the animals can hear you from a vast distance unless you are stationary. When an animal is shot quite often the tracks will criss cross your path without you ever seeing the animal moving in that direction, i have found often after shooting an animal in an open field the track criss crosses the field even though i had watched the animal run straight away from me and out of the field. I am not saying this game is a bad game by any means but there are glaring issues that havent been addressed. The game portrays itself as a hunting simulator with weather,wind,noise,fatigue but the animals are quite often based on an arcade style. I would happily recommend this game as a game to relax with but not as a game that rewards for progress and skill."
